        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Code verification acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Solver passes published FDA GCBP benchmark verification suite; order-of-accuracy confirmed for laminar pipe-flow manufactured solution."
      },
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent passes the FDA GCBP nozzle and backward-facing-step verification benchmarks. A manufactured-solution order-of-accuracy study for the laminar Navier–Stokes equations confirms second-order spatial convergence. Gradation 2 code-verification evidence is documented in the solver validation manual and reproduced in the project technical record."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/disc-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/disc-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Grid-convergence index (GCI) < 5% for normalised hemolysis index on three systematically refined meshes (coarse 2.1 M, medium 5.8 M, fine 14.2 M hexahedral cells)."
      },
      "rationale": "Three-level Richardson extrapolation and GCI analysis performed per Celik et al. (2008). GCI for the normalised hemolysis index is 3.2% (fine-to-medium) and 4.8% (medium-to-coarse), both below the 5% threshold. Apparent order of accuracy p = 1.94, consistent with the second-order discretisation scheme. Mesh convergence study documented in project report TR-GCBP-2024-02."
    },
    {
