        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation relevance acceptance criteria — MRL 2",
        "description": "Validation experiments performed on the same FDA GCBP geometry, same fluid, same operating range, and same measurement techniques as the COU simulation."
      },
      "rationale": "All validation activities use the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry (identical CAD file hash SHA-256:d4e5f6…), porcine blood surrogate with matched viscosity, and operating conditions spanning the full CPB envelope. PIV measurements and bench hemolysis tests were conducted in the same laboratory under the same protocol as the COU experiments. Validation-to-COU relevance mapping documented in VR-GCBP-2024-01 Section 4."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/num-solver-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 for a Class II device, explicit quantification of iterative solver residual error beyond standard convergence monitoring (residuals < 1e-5 for all equations, mass imbalance < 0.01%) is not required. Convergence behaviour is documented in run logs for all simulations. This factor is scoped out per the ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 credibility table, which does not mandate separate solver-error quantification at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/use-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use-error assessment (systematic evaluation of analyst-induced errors through independent simulation replication) is not required at MRL 2 for a Class II device. Simulation setup was peer-reviewed by a second analyst and discrepancies resolved prior to final runs. Formal use-error quantification is deferred to higher MRL assessments per the ASME V&V 40 credibility table."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal model-form uncertainty quantification (e.g., Bayesian model averaging across turbulence closures) is not required at MRL 2 for this Class II application. The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on published benchmark performance for rotating blood-pump flows (Hariharan et al. 2011). Sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to turbulence model choice is noted as a qualitative limitation in the project report but does not require formal quantification at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal parametric uncertainty propagation for all model inputs (geometry tolerances, fluid properties, boundary conditions) is not required at MRL 2. Nominal input values are traceable to calibrated measurements documented in lab notebook LN-GCBP-2024. A qualitative sensitivity discussion is included in the project report. Full probabilistic input uncertainty quantification is reserved for MRL 3+ assessments."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Statistical characterisation of test-sample variability (e.g., lot-to-lot variation in blood surrogate rheology or pump-geometry manufacturing tolerances across multiple pump specimens) is not required at MRL 2. A single representative pump specimen was used for all bench tests, consistent with the FDA GCBP benchmark protocol. Test-sample documentation is in lab notebook LN-GCBP-2024."
